table.body:
To apply for a court order, fill in the [C100 court form.](http://hmctsformfinder.direct.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2253){:rel="external"} 

Send it to your local [county court or family proceedings court.](http://hmctscourtfinder.direct.gov.uk/HMCTS/ "county court or family proceedings court"){:rel="external"}

A court order costs £200.

^You may be able to get help with [court fees](/court-fees-what-they-are/ "court fees") if you’re on benefits or a low income.^

You'll be asked to go to a court appointment. You may also have to go to a court hearing.

Judges and magistrates must always put the welfare of children first. They'll only make a court order if they think it's in the child's best interests.
